text: Tekeda Alemu (born in Addis Ababa, May 5, 1951) is a diplomat to the United Nations. He represents his country, Ethiopia. == Biography == Tekeda Alemu has served as a diplomat for many years, starting in 1983. For the month of September 2017, he served as the president of the United Nations Security Council. == References == Category:Living people Category:1951 births Category:Ethiopian politicians Category:Ambassadors to the United Nations
title: Tekeda Alemu
